@startuml sequence_chat_create
title Diagramme de Séquence — Envoi d'un message chat (Création de table)

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #7C3AED
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #7C3AED
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EDE7F6
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #7C3AED
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #F3E8FF
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #7C3AED
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam NoteBorderColor #FBC02D

actor "Utilisateur" as User
participant "ChatPanel\n(React)" as ChatUI
participant "useSession\n(hook)" as Hook
participant "API Client\n(lib/api.ts)" as API
participant "requireAuth\n(middleware)" as AuthMW
participant "Chat Route\n(Fastify)" as ChatRoute
participant "Claude Service\n(lib/claude.ts)" as Claude
participant "Anthropic API\n(Claude 3.5)" as AnthropicAPI
participant "PostgreSQL\n(pg pool)" as DB
participant "Canvas\n(React)" as Canvas

' ─── User sends a natural language prompt ─────────────────────────────────────
User -> ChatUI : Tape : "I run a restaurant.\nI need to track my menu items\nwith prices and my suppliers."
ChatUI -> Hook : sendMessage(text)

Hook -> Hook : Ajoute userMsg à messages[]\nAjoute typingMsg (loading indicator)
Hook -> API : sendChat(message, sessionId)
API -> ChatRoute : POST /api/chat\n{message, sessionId}\ncredentials: include

' ─── Auth check ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ChatRoute -> AuthMW : requireAuth(req, reply)
AuthMW -> AuthMW : Lit cookie morph_token\nverifyToken(token)
AuthMW --> ChatRoute : JwtPayload {userId, email}

' ─── Verify session ownership ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
ChatRoute -> DB : SELECT id FROM morph_sessions\nWHERE id=$1 AND user_id=$2
DB --> ChatRoute : [{id: 3}] ✓

' ─── Build session context ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ChatRoute -> DB : SELECT table_name\nFROM morph_session_tables\nWHERE session_id = $1
DB --> ChatRoute : [] (session vide)

ChatRoute -> DB : SELECT table_name, column_name, data_type\nFROM information_schema.columns\nWHERE table_name = ANY($1)
DB --> ChatRoute : [] (aucune table existante)

note over ChatRoute : Contexte = "No tables yet.\nUser is starting fresh."

' ─── Call Claude API ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ChatRoute -> Claude : generateSQL(userMessage, sessionContext)
Claude -> AnthropicAPI : Messages API\n- System prompt (SQL expert)\n- User message\n- Session context

note right of AnthropicAPI
  Le prompt système inclut:
  - Les tables existantes (schémas)
  - Le préfixe de session (s3_)
  - Les contraintes PostgreSQL
  - Le format JSON attendu
  en retour
end note

AnthropicAPI --> Claude : JSON response:\n{\n  action: "create_many",\n  tables: [\n    {name:"menu_items", columns:[...]},\n    {name:"suppliers", columns:[...]}\n  ],\n  sessionName: "Restaurant Manager"\n}

' ─── Parse & execute SQL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Claude --> ChatRoute : ParsedSQL {action, tables, sessionName}

loop Pour chaque table dans tables[]

  ChatRoute -> ChatRoute : Préfixe: "s3_menu_items", "s3_suppliers"\nGénère CREATE TABLE SQL

  ChatRoute -> DB : BEGIN TRANSACTION
  ChatRoute -> DB : CREATE TABLE s3_menu_items (\n  id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  name TEXT NOT NULL,\n  price DECIMAL(10,2),\n  category TEXT\n)
  DB --> ChatRoute : OK

  ChatRoute -> DB : INSERT INTO morph_session_tables\n(session_id, table_name, pos_x, pos_y)\nVALUES (3, 's3_menu_items', 80, 80)
  DB --> ChatRoute : OK

  ChatRoute -> DB : COMMIT
  DB --> ChatRoute : OK

end

' ─── Update session name ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ChatRoute -> DB : UPDATE morph_sessions\nSET name='Restaurant Manager'\nWHERE id=3
DB --> ChatRoute : OK

' ─── Persist assistant message ────────────────────────────────────────────────
ChatRoute -> DB : INSERT INTO morph_messages\n(session_id, role, text)\nVALUES (3, 'system', 'I created 2 tables...')
DB --> ChatRoute : OK

' ─── Build response with full schema ─────────────────────────────────────────
ChatRoute -> DB : SELECT column_name, data_type, is_nullable\nFROM information_schema.columns\nWHERE table_name = 's3_menu_items'
DB --> ChatRoute : [{name, price, category, ...}]

ChatRoute --> API : HTTP 200 ChatResponse {\n  action: "create_many",\n  schemas: [...],\n  message: "Created menu_items and suppliers",\n  sessionName: "Restaurant Manager",\n  columnSources: {...}\n}

' ─── Frontend update ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
API --> Hook : ChatResponse

Hook -> Hook : Retire typingMsg\nAjoute message assistant
Hook -> Hook : Met à jour sessionName\ndans sessions[]
Hook -> Hook : addOrUpdateTable("s3_menu_items", x, y)\naddOrUpdateTable("s3_suppliers", x+360, y)

' ─── Fetch FK relations ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Hook -> API : getSessionRelations(sessionId)
API -> DB : (voir diagramme relations)
DB --> API : {relations: [{from: "s3_orders", to: "s3_menu_items", on: "menu_item"}]}
API --> Hook : {relations}
Hook -> Hook : setRelations(fresh)

Hook --> ChatUI : messages[] mis à jour
Hook --> Canvas : tables[] mis à jour

Canvas -> Canvas : Rend <TableCard> pour\nchaque table
Canvas -> Canvas : Dessine les connecteurs FK\n(SVG overlay)

Canvas --> User : ✅ 2 cartes apparaissent sur le canvas\navec les colonnes et les données

note over User, Canvas
  L'utilisateur voit instantanément
  les tables "menu_items" et "suppliers"
  positionnées sur le canvas interactif.
  Il peut drag-and-drop les cartes,
  cliquer pour voir/éditer les données.
end note

@enduml
